I always love a SCP with a well executed bomb drop at the end, and this was absolutely that. I very genuinely say, I had my finger on the -1 trigger because I was not at all interested in a story about a Dead Sea copy. You made those final few lines fill me with such a heavy sense of dread and interest that was completely redeeming. I believe there were some flaws in your earlier draft, but this injunction with the tale felt flawless to me and left me wanting more. Given, the tale was sort of a necessity to understand, but it was short and clear for the most part so they both got a happy +1.







